# BetterCallClaude — Local Playbook

<!-- Save this file as:
     - .claude/bettercallclaude.local.md  (Claude Code, per-project)
     - or in a shared folder                (Cowork Desktop)
     Adapt the sections to your law firm/legal department.
     The language of this playbook determines the default output language. -->

## Firm / Legal Department Profile

- **Name**: [Firm / company name]
- **Seat**: [City, canton]
- **Main cantons**: [e.g. ZH, GE, VD]
- **Working languages**: [e.g. EN, DE]
- **Default language for output and citations**: EN
- **Type**: Law firm | In-house | Fiduciary

## Standard Contractual Positions

- **Governing law**: Swiss law (CISG exclusion: yes/no)
- **Jurisdiction**: [Firm seat; Swiss Rules arbitration clause: yes/no]
- **Limitation of liability**: Acceptable cap [e.g. contract value]; never-acceptable exclusions [e.g. personal injury]
  — Note: intent and gross negligence are mandatory (Art. 100 CO)
- **Liquidated damages**: Acceptable thresholds [e.g. max 10% of contract value] (Art. 160 et seq. CO)
- **Term and termination**: Standard preferences [e.g. 12 months, 3-month notice period]
- **NDA**: Maximum acceptable duration [e.g. 5 years]; scope of "confidential information" definition

## Risk Thresholds and Escalation

- **Threshold for mandatory human review**: [e.g. amount in dispute > CHF 500,000]
- **Clauses that always trigger escalation**:
  - Unlimited warranties
  - Waiver of mandatory rights (zwingendes Recht)
  - Derogations from Art. 100 CO (liability for intent/gross negligence)
  - [Add more as needed]
- **Escalation recipient**: [Role, e.g. managing partner / general counsel]

## Data Protection

- **Typical role**: Controller / processor
- **Recurring cross-border transfers**: [e.g. EU, USA — adequacy decision / SCCs]
- **Standard DPA**: [e.g. nFADP template / internal template]

## Style and Format

- **Citation format**: [e.g. BGE 144 III 462 E. 3.2; Art. 97(1) CO]
- **Output format**: Memo / Redline / Table
- **Citation language**: EN (with Swiss references)
